Update on SCP launch issues
text: I spoke to Ken on the phone. The root cause is that a piece of VMS that resolves domain names to IP addresses has crashed, and cannot be rebooted. This is why the mccscp and eoicdesk VMS accounts don't work: They are restricted to only work from certain computers, and with the domain name resolution not functional, VMS can't verify what machine you are logging in from. He has a potential fix for the problem, and he is testing it on mccdev right now. If it works, he will have to reboot mcc to deploy it. I asked that if his fix doesn't work, could we remove the restrictions on mccscp and eoicdesk to let you use them from anywhere - he said he'll look into it, but doesn't immediately know how those restrictions are implemented.
